           SPELL=qvwm
         VERSION=1.1.12
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-${VERSION}.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}-${VERSION}
   SOURCE_URL[0]=ftp://ftp.qvwm.org/pub/qvwm/${SOURCE}
   SOURCE_URL[1]=http://www.qvwm.org/archive/qvwm/${SOURCE}
          MD5[0]=c2f4a4b2c0260fdcf98dd4ff2b9592c1
        WEB_SITE=http://www.qvwm.org/
         ENTERED=20040204
         UPDATED=20040204
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
       BUILD_API=2
           SHORT="Windows(R) 95/98/NT(R)-like window manager"
cat << EOF
Qvwm is a Windows(R) 95/98/NT(R)-like window manager for the X Window System. It allows Windows(R) 95/98/NT(R) users to use the X Window System without hesitation and X Window System users to use Windows(R) 95/98/NT(R) without hesitation.
Features:
* Written with C++ from scratch
* Internationalized without patches
* The same graphics with Windows(R) 95(R) at a pixel level
* Enables the user to switch among windows using the task switcher (Alt+Tab)
* Enables the user to make some windows taskbar indicators
* Enables the user to move and resize a whole window (full-drag)
* Virtual screen (extension of Windows(R) 95(R))
* Dialog box on termination
* Titlebar animation on minimizing/maximizing a window
EOF
